      "id": "RQ-0019",
      "status": "todo",
      "title": "Refresh the local command reference to the installed agent-browser surface",
      "description": "Principles: Least astonishment, Consistency/Integrity.\n\nEvidence:\n- path: docs/COMMAND_REFERENCE.md:11-13 :: the file claims to be the repo-readable equivalent of the upstream command surface for blocked direct-binary sessions.\n- path: docs/REQUIREMENTS.md:67-68 :: requirements say the local command reference must stay in sync with the effective agent_browser surface.\n- workflow: agent-browser --version :: local upstream version is `0.26.0`.\n- workflow: agent-browser --help :: current help includes major surface area not represented in docs/COMMAND_REFERENCE.md, including `skills`, `keyboard`, `scroll`, `scrollintoview`, `is`, `find`, `mouse`, `set`, `network`, `storage`, `diff`, `trace`, `record`, `stream`, `auth`, `confirm`, `deny`, `chat`, `dashboard`, `doctor`, `profiles`, `snapshot --urls`, and `wait --download`.\n- workflow: agent-browser tab --help; agent-browser snapshot --help; agent-browser wait --help :: subcommand help confirms current options that the local reference does not enumerate.\n\nWhy it matters: this repo explicitly positions the local command reference as the fallback for blocked binary help. Right now it materially understates the command surface available to the extension's target upstream version on this machine.\n\nMinimal proposed fix: re-baseline docs/COMMAND_REFERENCE.md against the currently installed `agent-browser` help output, clearly separate the core recommended workflow from the full supported surface, and add a lightweight verification step that catches future upstream drift.\n\nAcceptance criteria: the command reference reflects the installed upstream 0.26.0 command and option surface relevant to this project; recommended workflows stay concise while a full or linked reference covers the rest; add a drift check against `agent-browser --help` or a maintained snapshot; verify `npm run verify`, `npm run verify:package`, and `npm run verify:package:pi` remain green.",
