      "id": "RQ-0013",
      "status": "todo",
      "title": "Unify the agent_browser playbook and fix current doc drift",
      "description": "Principles: DRY knowledge, Least astonishment, Consistency/Integrity.\n\nEvidence:\n- path: README.md:213-228 :: README describes inspection support using shell-like `agent_browser --help` wording and documents post-command tab restoration.\n- path: docs/COMMAND_REFERENCE.md:226-256 :: the command reference documents stateless `--help` and `--version` but omits the post-command tab-restoration behavior that the wrapper currently implements.\n- path: docs/REQUIREMENTS.md:99-104 :: requirements require the local command reference and prompt guidance to stay in sync with wrapper behavior, including post-command tab restoration.\n- path: docs/TOOL_CONTRACT.md:28-29,184-193 :: the tool contract repeats the same playbook rules and explicitly includes post-command tab restoration.\n- path: extensions/agent-browser/index.ts:70-99 :: prompt guidance hard-codes another copy of the same workflow rules inside the extension.\n\nWhy it matters: the repo currently has several hand-maintained copies of the same agent-facing workflow. They are already drifting, which makes the local command reference less reliable for the exact browser-recovery edge cases the wrapper is supposed to clarify.\n\nMinimal proposed fix: move the shared playbook text to one canonical source or generated fragment, update README and COMMAND_REFERENCE to use actual tool-call shapes, and restore any omitted behavior notes that are part of the effective wrapper surface.\n\nAcceptance criteria: README, COMMAND_REFERENCE, and tool guidance describe the same inspection path and recovery behaviors; the command reference includes the currently implemented post-command tab restoration behavior; add a lightweight regression check or generation step that prevents future drift; verify `npm run verify` still passes.",
      "priority": "medium",
      "tags": [
        "maintenance",
        "docs",
        "dry",
        "agent-browser"
      ],
      "scope": [
        "README.md",
        "docs/COMMAND_REFERENCE.md",
