      "id": "RQ-0020",
      "status": "todo",
      "title": "Resolve the mixed -e versus /reload local-validation workflow",
      "description": "Principles: Least astonishment, Consistency/Integrity.\n\nEvidence:\n- path: AGENTS.md:85-96 :: repo guidance prescribes local checkout validation with `pi --no-extensions -e .` and still requires `/reload` or full restart validation after extension changes.\n- path: README.md:173-200,209-223 :: README tells maintainers to keep the checkout path enabled in Pi settings, launch with `pi --no-extensions -e .`, and validate `/reload` or restart plus `/resume`.\n- path: docs/REQUIREMENTS.md:73-79 :: requirements also prescribe `/reload` validation in the local workflow.\n- external: /opt/homebrew/lib/node_modules/@mariozechner/pi-coding-agent/docs/extensions.md :: accessed 2026-04-27 :: Pi's own extension docs say `pi -e ./path.ts` is for quick tests, while `/reload` applies to auto-discovered extension locations.\n- workflow: pi --help :: `--no-extensions` disables extension discovery while explicit `-e` paths still work, confirming the repo is mixing two loading models in one workflow description.\n\nWhy it matters: maintainers are being told to validate hot reload while also being told to launch in a mode that bypasses extension discovery. That makes it unclear which extension path `/reload` is actually exercising and can create false confidence about local checkout validation.\n\nMinimal proposed fix: choose one canonical local-validation workflow for hot-reload testing versus quick isolated `-e` testing, document the tradeoff explicitly, and remove contradictory instructions about Pi settings and `/reload` from the non-canonical path.\n\nAcceptance criteria: README, AGENTS, and requirements describe one coherent local-validation workflow for `/reload` and one coherent quick-test workflow for `-e`; the docs explain when Pi settings should or should not matter; verify the updated instructions against Pi's extension docs and `pi --help`.",
      "priority": "medium",
      "tags": [
        "maintenance",
        "docs",
        "workflow",
        "pi"
      ],
      "scope": [
        "AGENTS.md",
        "README.md",
        "docs/REQUIREMENTS.md",
        "/opt/homebrew/lib/node_modules/@mariozechner/pi-coding-agent/docs/extensions.md",
        "pi --help"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "path: AGENTS.md:85-96 :: local validation instructions combine `pi --no-extensions -e .` with `/reload` expectations",
        "path: README.md:173-200,209-223 :: README mixes Pi settings guidance, isolated -e loading, and `/reload` expectations in the same workflow",
        "path: docs/REQUIREMENTS.md:73-79 :: requirements also prescribe `/reload` in the local validation path",
        "external: /opt/homebrew/lib/node_modules/@mariozechner/pi-coding-agent/docs/extensions.md :: accessed 2026-04-27 :: Pi docs reserve `/reload` for auto-discovered extension locations, not ad hoc `-e` quick tests",
        "workflow: pi --help :: `--no-extensions` disables extension discovery while explicit `-e` paths still work"
      ],
      "plan": [
        "Decide which local validation path is canonical for hot reload and which is canonical for isolated quick tests.",
        "Update AGENTS, README, and requirements so each path has consistent setup steps, Pi settings expectations, and reload or restart guidance.",
